</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="1006" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1058,1293,1344]" pageId="47" pageNumber="1006">
E t y m o l o g y: The name 
<emphasis box="[467,584,1293,1314]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="1006">Nanoclerus</emphasis>
stems from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[811,871,1293,1314]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="1006">nanus</emphasis>
(= dwarf) and the checkered beetle genus name 
<emphasis box="[454,528,1322,1343]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="1006">Clerus.</emphasis>
The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
